==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irk
<hw>Irk</hw> <pr>(⟦etil⟧rk)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>irken</ets> to tire, become tired; cf. Sw. <ets>yrka</ets> to urge,
enforce, press, or G. <ets>ekel</ets> disgust, MHG. <ets>erklich</ets>
disgusting; perh. akin to L. <ets>urgere</ets> to urge, E.
<ets>urge</ets>.]</ety> <def>To weary; to give pain; to annoy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To see this sight, it <qex>irks</qex> my very soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It <qex>irketh</qex> him to be here.</q> <rj><qau>M.
Arnold.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irksome</ent>⟦br⟧
